<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-212-036 </DOCNO><DOCID>09 826 659</DOCID><JOURNAL>Macworld  March 1991 v8 n3 p177(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Cheshire 1.0. (Software Review) (Abbott Systems charting utility)(evaluation)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Bishop, Philip.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Abbott Systems' $125 Cheshire 1.0 is an add-in charting utilityfor Macintosh word processors that creates simple, no-frillsgraphs using 21 built-in chart types.andP;  It runs as an INIT and canbe called up via a hot-key from Microsoft Word 3 and 4, MacWriteII, MacDraw II and PageMaker 3 and 4.andP;  The program uses a standardtab-delimited format and lets the user select any installed font.andO;Graph options include white, black and gray grid lines; dropshadows; backgrounds; and a 'Plot White' feature that gives theeffect of reversing the chart shape.andP;  Users can edit charts at anytime from within other applications and quickly paste them intodocuments.andP;  Cheshire 1.0 unfortunately lacks a pie chart, butAbbott Systems says this will be an option in the next version.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Abbott Systems Inc. (Products).andO;Product:   Apple Macintosh (Microcomputer) (Computer programs)Cheshire (Add-in/on software).andO;Topic:     Graphics SoftwareEvaluationChartsUtility Programs.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>